Day 19 - Let‚Äôs Get Blitzen: Cocktail Advent Calendar - Cranberry Sauce Sour.

The holidays should be spent enjoying time with family and friends, not with your kitchenware. This make-ahead cranberry sauce is equally delicious with your turkey and in your cocktails made with Canadian @eggsoeufs . [AD]

Cranberry Sauce Sour

- 1¬Ω oz pisco OR non-alcoholic spirit of your choosing
- ¬æ oz cranberry sauce (recipe on the blog)
- ¬æ oz lemon juice
- ¬Ω oz sage champagne syrup (recipe on the blog)
- 1 egg white
- Garnish: 3 candied or fresh cranberries

- Add all ingredients to a shaker and dry shake for 15-20 seconds. Add ice and shake again until well-chilled.
- Strain into a chilled coupe glass.
- Garnish with 3 candied or fresh cranberries skewered on a cocktail pick.

Eggs, choline & your memory!

Eggs naturally contain choline, a nutrient that may play a role in memory.

Some studies suggest that adequate choline intake throughout adult life may improve cognitive function later in life.

Researchers at Boston University School of Medicine found that higher intakes of choline were related to better cognitive performance such as verbal memory and visual memory. https://doi.org/10.3945/ajcn.110.008938

Since our body only makes a very small amount of choline, we need to get this important nutrient from foods such as eggs.

Eggs are one of the best dietary sources of choline. Two large eggsü•öü•öcontain 75% of your daily needs for choline.
